                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15187856" author="philipthompson" created="Wed, 9 Mar 2016 20:24:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is not happening on 2.2.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15188955" author="beobal" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2016 09:29:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The IF NOT EXISTS check for indexes only validates that no other index &lt;b&gt;with the same name&lt;/b&gt; exists and as you&apos;re not specifying a name for the index, a generated one will be used which is guaranteed to be unique, so the IF NOT EXISTS check passes. The creation then fails as observed because the index duplicates the existing one semantically (i.e. in everything but the name). This is new behaviour in 3.0 as previously the 1:1 relationship between indexes and columns prevented a duplicate indexes anyway.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So at the moment, this is behaving as expected but we can broaden the scope of the IF NOT EXISTS check to include duplicates in all but name.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15188963" author="slebresne" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2016 09:35:46 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;we can broaden the scope of the IF NOT EXISTS check to include duplicates in all but name&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we should. And honestly, from a user point of view, this sounds a lot like a regression and it&apos;s hard to argue it&apos;s not.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15189677" author="beobal" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2016 18:25:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Pushed a branch in which the &lt;tt&gt;IF NOT EXISTS&lt;/tt&gt; clause is applied to a duplicate-in-all-but-name. It merges cleanly to 3.5 and trunk, where the relevant unit tests also pass, so I didn&apos;t trigger additional CI on those branches.&lt;/p&gt;

